The paper proposes a model for analyzing shopping transactions by learning product representations from textual contents such as product titles. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Language and Speech Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The model also involves classification and learning vector representations, which are common in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with large datasets and efficient modeling, which are relevant to the Database (cs.DB) sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CE, and cs.DB, in that order.
